tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE Gene_Editing_Techniques (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    technique_name VARCHAR(255),
    technique_description TEXT,
    researcher_name VARCHAR(255),
    success_rate DECIMAL
)

CREATE TABLE ExperimentalData (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    technique_id INT,
    researcher_name TEXT,
    experiment_date DATE,
    outcome TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (technique_id) REFERENCES GeneEditingTechniques(technique_id)
);

CREATE TABLE gene_editing_techniques (
    technique_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    technique_name VARCHAR(255),
    description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE outcomes (
    outcome_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    outcome_name VARCHAR(255),
    result VARCHAR(255),
    success BOOLEAN
)

CREATE TABLE researchers (
    researcher_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    researcher_name VARCHAR(255),
    affiliation VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE experiments (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    technique_id INT,
    outcome_id INT,
    researcher_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (technique_id) REFERENCES gene_editing_techniques(technique_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (outcome_id) REFERENCES outcomes(outcome_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (researcher_id) REFERENCES researchers(researcher_id)
)

CREATE TABLE GeneEditingTechniques (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
name VARCHAR(50),
description TEXT,
researcher VARCHAR(100),
publication_date DATE);

CREATE TABLE TargetGenes (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
gene_name VARCHAR(50),
organism VARCHAR(50),
chromosome VARCHAR(10),
start_position INT,
end_position INT);

CREATE TABLE EditingEffects (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
editing_method VARCHAR(50),
effect VARCHAR(50),
effect_description TEXT,
accuracy DECIMAL(5, 2));

CREATE TABLE ResearchGroups (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
name VARCHAR(100),
location VARCHAR(100),
research_area VARCHAR(200),
leader VARCHAR(100));

CREATE TABLE ExperimentResults (id INT PRIMARY KEY,
experiment_date DATE,
success BOOLEAN,
effect_id INT,
FOREIGN KEY (effect_id) REFERENCES EditingEffects(id));
